BENIN – Hon. Dennis Idahosa, members representing Ovia Federal Constituency of Edo State, has said that Super Eagles are giving Nigerians something to be hopeful for with their current display in the ongoing Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) in Cameroon. Idahosa stated this in his reaction to the Eagles 3 – 1 victory against Sudan on Saturday. The lawmaker who described football as a unifying factor among people of the World, said Eagles tend to make Nigerians forget about the challenges confronting the nation whenever they are playing. 2023: Electoral Amendment Bill: Stakeholders Urge NASS To… Convention: APC Governors In Crucial Meeting He noted that irrespective of tribe and ethnicity, the only discussion among Nigerians was the match between Nigeria and the Northeastern African team. “It was a cherish victory and i dare say that it gave Nigerians to temporarily forget about our problems in addition to giving us something to be hopeful for. “There is no use pretending, the nation’s challenges are enormous, especially the issue of insecurity; you will see how happy our people were seeing Eagles play and winning their matches in the ongoing AFCON. “Like I said in their first match against Egypt, the Eagles must keep this winning mentality and play every match as if it is their last match. “They (Eagles) are the only thing that keeps Nigerians happy now and should be made to understand this. A lot rest on their shoulders and must not disappoint. POLL Eagles defeated the Sudanese through goals scored by Kelechi Iheanacho, Moses Simon and Taiwo Awoniyi while the Sudanese scores thwir consolatory goal through penalty. The Nigeria team last group match will be against Guinea-Bissau.